## Layout

```
{{.ProjectName}}/                  # this directory (git-versioned)
  .gitignore               # allowlist: only tracks .gitignore, .mws.toml, .mws/, README.md
  .mws.toml                # mws config (project name, repos, env mappings)
  .mws/                    # harness; everything here symlinks into every working copy
  .envs/                   # env staging (per-repo files, copied into working copies on clone)
  main/                    # first working copy created by `mws init`
  <peer>/                  # any number of peer working copies created via `mws clone`
```

## Conventions

- Edit harness content under `.mws/`. Working copies see the change instantly through symlinks.
- New top-level files added directly in a working copy stay local until you `mws promote <path>` them into `.mws/`.
- Native repos inside each working copy are independent git clones -- every working copy has its own `.git/` inside each repo dir.
- Env files: populate them in a working copy, then `mws stage-env <copy>` to capture defaults. Subsequent `mws clone` reproduces them automatically. `mws sync-env <copy>` resets a copy back to staged defaults.
